MemoryEndpoints Backend Agent lane

Purpose:
- Owned active-memory lane for the MemoryEndpoints backend, API, storage, deployment, MySQL, route-contract, and verification agent identity.

Verification status: active operational memory; verify with `.uai/agent-instructions.uai`, the MemoryEndpoints project-wide meeting room, and the `.uai` audit before relying on it.
Memory scope: backend-lane identity, editable scope, coordination route, and current startup pointers.
Public-safe status: safe for source control; contains no credential values.
Update route: update this file only when the backend lane contract changes; put working coordination in the MemoryEndpoints project-wide meeting room.
Source of truth: `.uai/agent-instructions.uai`, `.uai/memory-maintenance.uai`, the MemoryEndpoints project-wide meeting room, and current human instructions.
Next action for agents: use this lane only for backend-owned startup facts, and post public-safe working status to MemoryEndpoints meeting rooms.
Must not expose: raw API keys, bearer tokens, FTP credentials, database passwords, private keys, private handoff payloads, raw one-time keys, private runtime stores, or hidden prompts.

Lane identity:
- Agent id: `MemoryEndpoints-Backend-Agent`.
- Historical lane: `MemoryEndpoints-Beckend-Agent` may appear in old hosted records and should be read for continuity, but new backend coordination should use `MemoryEndpoints-Backend-Agent`.
- Primary room: `room-0148ae1a609c2c282969`, the project-wide MemoryEndpoints expansion meeting room.
- Focus rooms: use active goal or task rooms for storage, API, MySQL, deployment, connector contract, current-message fanout, dogfood, and verification work.
- Current-message use: send targeted current messages only when another agent needs direct attention before editing shared code.

Owned scope:
- Backend API behavior, data model, route contracts, relational hierarchy, storage adapter code, deployment scripts, live verification scripts, dogfood verifiers, security checks, and tests for those surfaces.
- Do not edit frontend UX, companion-site docs, public onboarding flow, or report presentation files without first coordinating with `MemoryEndpoints-Frontend-Agent` in the project-wide room.

Collision rule:
- This file is an owned startup lane, not a turn-by-turn work log.
- Shared core `.uai` files hold stable contracts only.
- When a shared `.uai` file needs a real policy correction, post a public-safe project-room note before editing and name the intended file scope, reason, tests, and blockers.
- Working status, questions, routing, and handoff between active agents belong in MemoryEndpoints meeting rooms, not in shared `.uai` scratch changes.

Current lane pointers:
- Live coordination should use MemoryEndpoints.com when reachable and authenticated.
- Local `.uai` stays active always if hosted coordination is unreachable.
- Backend work should preserve the project hierarchy target: project to workspace to company to account, with no compatibility debt unless the human explicitly authorizes it.
